    {
        "content": "<p>why do you wrap the expr fragments with <code>$()</code>? That shouldn't be necessary</p>",
        "id": 502919583,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1740964249
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, I copied that from the official Rust book's chapter on macros (20.5). I assumed it would be harmless without a pattern match, but I see I was wrong after trying that change. A quick follow-up question regarding the following error.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[macro_export]</span>\n<span class=\"fm\">macro_rules!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">usb_device</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">vendor</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$vendor</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"nc\">expr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">product</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$product</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"nc\">expr</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">DeviceId</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Opaque</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">hid_device_id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">bus</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mh\">0x3</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cm\">/* BUS_USB */</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">vendor</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$($vendor</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">product</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$($product</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: The rest is zeroed out to initialize `struct hid_device_id`,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// sets `Option&lt;&amp;F&gt;` to be `None`.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$crate</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">mem</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">hid_device_id</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">zeroed</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">assume_init</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">expected</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">one</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">hid</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">161</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">13</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">161</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">             </span><span class=\"n\">product</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$($product</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">             </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 502920125,
        "sender_full_name": "Rahul Rameshbabu",
        "timestamp": 1740964631
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's a similar problem. An excessive <code>$()</code>... Any good resources on <code>macro_rules!</code> compared to the book?</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch20-06-macros.html\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch20-06-macros.html</a></p>",
        "id": 502920331,
        "sender_full_name": "Rahul Rameshbabu",
        "timestamp": 1740964793
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for the help here. This helped me out with my other macros as well. Hoping to have functioning hid bindings and a driver very soon to post an initial RFC.</p>",
        "id": 502920659,
        "sender_full_name": "Rahul Rameshbabu",
        "timestamp": 1740965015
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"667402\">Rahul Rameshbabu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/error.3A.20.60.24vendor.3Aexpr.60.20is.20followed.20by.20.60.3A.60.2C.20which.20is.20not.20allow/near/502920125\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yeah, I copied that from the official Rust book's chapter on macros (20.5). I assumed it would be harmless without a pattern match, but I see I was wrong after trying that change.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Note that in that chapter, there is a star (<code>*</code>) after the comma, that means that it can match the inner part of the parenthesis any number of times (including 0), while also matching a separating comma between matches.</p>",
        "id": 502923213,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1740966744
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"667402\">Rahul Rameshbabu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/error.3A.20.60.24vendor.3Aexpr.60.20is.20followed.20by.20.60.3A.60.2C.20which.20is.20not.20allow/near/502920331\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It's a similar problem. An excessive <code>$()</code>... Any good resources on <code>macro_rules!</code> compared to the book?</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch20-06-macros.html\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch20-06-macros.html</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>here you're also missing a <code>*</code> after the <code>)</code> (but you probably don't want to match multiple, hence you can just remove it)</p>",
        "id": 502923262,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1740966781
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't know of any good resource for simple macros like this one. for more complex ones, there is: <a href=\"https://veykril.github.io/tlborm/\">https://veykril.github.io/tlborm/</a></p>",
        "id": 502923385,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1740966860
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"546447\">@Benno Lossin</span> Thanks, I understand now from the book that was needed for things like pattern repeating, but I guess I felt that from reading the chapter alone, it would be harmless to leave the outer <code>$()</code>.  I'll take a look at the language docs and that link you shared for more. Macros are definitely the area I struggle the most. The rest of my Rust code just compiled after resolving macro issues.</p>",
        "id": 502924253,
        "sender_full_name": "Rahul Rameshbabu",
        "timestamp": 1740967481
    },
